channel.title: [Server ControlPanel] [PI 317] [InsidiaX V1] Simple help
channel.description: Hello guys, I've been googling around looking for TUTS on Control Panel, but it seems like there are only TUTS from "2011 and 2012" Which I tried but doesn't work :S Errors. Anyways, I was wondering if anyone could help me with making a Control Panel. I have a InsidiaX V1 Source/Base. Any help would be greatly appreciated. Thank you.

item.title: [Server ControlPanel] [PI 317] [InsidiaX V1] Simple help
item.dc:creator: @imback4more imback4more
item.description:
@imback4more wrote:

[quote=“malimt, post:6, topic:547352”][quote author=sk8rdude461 link=topic=666258.msg4454349#msg4454349 date=1413754834]

Get eclipse.
Open your project in it.
Get Eclipse window builder.
Make a control panel using that.

I was looking for a TUT to use, I don’t really like using eclipse for my server.
Thanks though/:

Then use netbeans. You’re not using it for your server. You’re using the window builder to make the console. It’s basically a WYSIWYG editor for java panels. Otherwise you’ll have to type it all up.
http://java.about.com/od/creatinguserinterfaces/ss/Example-Java-Code-For-Building-A-Simple-Gui-Application.htm
[/quote]
Alright then, Thanks man.
Still hoping for other options or tuts /:[/quote]

I bet you have NO IDEA what he just said, do you? :L

Read full topic
